caption: When the delivery service doesn't show, so someone personally drives your pizza to you. Awesome staff!  Then the pizza. Our eyes were greeted with a speckled circle of cheese, bread, and what we could infer to be thin crust goodness. Both the first bite and the last failed to disappoint, as the pie struck a perfect balanced trifecta of classicly savory pizza notes, spicy pepperoni, and fingerlicking sweet honey - it certainly was a pie that had all of the right moves.
Best burger in the U.S. in my opinion and that's not even mentioning the 🔥pizzas and general atmosphere. This place is Awesome!!! 😎 Also the salads are phenomenal if that's your thing
great burger, great pizza. love this place
I like to commend their staff for serving us politely, and thanks to these guys that managed to provide us a good pizza and pasta. I will surely recommend this restaurant to everyone! Thanks a lot!
Amazing spot for pizza. Almost all the right things is fantastic

Burger was juicy and flavorful + fluffy bun with perfect coating. Shoestring fries were great. Wild Honey Pie was good but the honey seemed out of place with other ingredients. Great, quick customer service!
Best burgers in Chicago.  Try the stop in.

We’ve been wanting to try this place for a long time. We’ve been looking for a good NY style pizza forever and were under the impression that they had it. Well, they didn’t but we were so pleasantly surprised! The pizza that we got were amazing. So much so that we ordered two more to go! The pizza is more Neapolitan style. They don’t have indoor dining but they have plenty of outdoor tables and have streamlined the ordering and payment process. It all done from your phone. From the menu to the bill. It was very easy and we felt safe with the restrictions. We will be coming back!

Easily my favorite casual dining spot in town! Best burger 🍔 two juicy patties with American cheese, and fries are unbeatable for the price (at least in this area)! Pizza is also excellent! Servers are always nice and honest about their menu favorites. They even have gluten free pizza and buns. We love coming here after a long bike ride!
My best kept secret, but it’s no longer a good time to keep secrets. Please add the Stop-In Burger to every list of the best burgers in Chicago. It is perfect, you won’t be disappointed.

So cute!

Fantastic burgers, pizza and ambience.

Never again - called in a delivery order, the call didn’t go through twice, they lied about having Kalamata olives (green olives are not the same), and then they (or DoorDash) called back to say it would cost even more since I ordered extra toppings.  Now, I appreciated the gluten free crust and vegan cheese, but my stomach is not thanking me the next day.  One small pizza + one large pizza delivered = $62 🤨
Excellent food, environment, and friendly staff/ownership!
The place offers a nice range of delicious food. I enjoyed eating here. Employees are always very friendly, pricing is convenient and the place is always clean.

Great vibe and food (the garlic knots and soft serve with olive oil and sea salt were delicious)! Friendly owner and staff. We are visiting from NYC and would definitely go back!
Fantastic staff, even better food! Definitely recommend for pizza or the burger. People have been sleeping on this burger, one of the best in the Chi.

We absolutely love this place. It's great for kids, the hamburgers are best in the city, the pizza is delicious (get the hot honey on it, amazing), the service is great and friendly. I'm not even kidding, between delivery and eating in, we get stop along about twice a month. Also...no better way to end the meal than with soft serve ice cream with olive oil and sea salt.
wait time is ridiculous

Excellent double burg! The beer/shot/burger special is a steal.
Definitely some of the best pizza in the city, very flavorful with super fresh ingredients.

This place is so awesome. Tiny, a little off the grid, and super delicious. The menu is really small, but I still had trouble deciding what to order. My friend ordered the arugula, tomato sauce, and mascarpone pizza and it might have been the best pizza either of us has ever had. Finished up with the flourless chocolate cake, which was divine. Overall an excellent spiritual food journey. Pretty casual, staff is friendly, and at ~$25 per person I'd say it was definitely a treat I will be having again!

$15 for the Stop-In Burger, beer, and a shot! The burger was a double patty, patties were thin, diner-style. The sauce on the burger remind me of Big Mac sauce, but tastier and less processed. Fries were decent, good but nothing spectacular. I'd love to come back and try their pizza.
Great Pizza and customer service. Love the Classic toys displayed all around the bar. Oh and not to mention the bill arrives on a Nintendo game cartridge

Visited last night (11/8/2019)for the first time. This place is awesome. It's kid friendly. They serve drinks for adults, bartender is excellent, the cook/chef deserves an award. We ordered bacon, double cheeseburgers with everything ( no tomatoes for me) with salads instead of fries. The food was just the best, burgers melted in our mouths. My best friend and I wanted to find someplace to eat before a show on Chicago's North side, needless to say we'll be back. Excellent!!!

This place is awesome. I've never seen it packed & it surprises me! Burger is GREAT - a block from Small Cheval & I think it's better! Sweet 80s/90s decor & TV media/movies playing. Down to earth employees. Lots of booze to choose from - can add to milkshakes, too! Garlic knots & doughnut bites are all good. I've heard pizza is good, but I can't stop eating the burgers, knots, & doughnuts
Great food! Got the burger, beer and shot deal.

Garlic knots were good but other items (burger, salad) were meh. Service was a little odd but we were on the patio (sidewalk). We'll have to go back and try the pizza though!

Tasty burgers and pizza with gluten free options. One of my all time favorite pizza crusts. Will visit anytime we are in Chicago. Relaxed, family friendly atmosphere. Loud when busy for those who have sensory issues best to eat outside or enjoy during a lull service time.

Firstly. How's the pizza? It's incredible, genuinely one of the best in Chicago. It's like the pizza you would see in cartoons growing up that looked incredible and wondered how damn good it would taste. This is that pizza. It's real. Seriously, just get a Coke and a slice of cheese and if you're not happy then you are beyond help.  Secondly. The atmosphere? Imagine taking the best parts of 80s pop culture and building a pizzeria with it. Seriously, there's a mural of the teenage mutant Ninja turtles pained on the back of the building. Which you can admire riding the blue line just south of the Western stop.  Bottom line: In a city where average pizza is world class anywhere else The StopAlong manages to stand out in both taste and style.  Pro tip: Soft Serve Ice Cream with Olive Oil. No joke.
Great place to grab a drink and something to eat
Great find, I'll be back.

I know people say it's just supposed to be In N Out but it is way more than that. Great size, perfectly cooked. The fries were great, the little dough knots were amazing, the beer list was diverse, and everything was super reasonable for Bucktown prices. Wait staff was very attentive.

(There's a hidden meaning behind the fish). Great food, awesome atmosphere. Don't ask for water.....tastes like sewer! Awesome burger picture included, great service, great decor, awesome specials check it out! They have happy hour menu! Worth coming out for quick bite and a casual date! Sitting for one or groups! Definitely worth bang for buck! Definitely recommend it!!!!!

Absolutely everything we had was incredible. The pizza was phenomenal, and all have awesome themes. The burger was just as good. Yeah, I ate a burger and pizza... who cares. I’ll run it off in the morning! Don’t judge my lifestyle. You try sitting there eating a burger and constantly smelling pizza cooking and see how long you hold out. I regret nothing and will chalk this up to an epic cheat meal.  But seriously, fantastic food and even better staff. The menu is deep with specialty pizzas and can’t wait to try more. good pizza and sandwiches. The cookie unskillet dessert is awesome. I had the chicken sandwich and my wife and daughter split a pizza. The chicken sandwich was very good and the french fries were even better.

If you grew up in the 80s/90s, and you're also looking for a fantastic pizza, this place is for you. Normally I try to avoid the themed restaurants as you usually find their food lacks something to be desired. I went in on a Saturday evening with my boyfriend, and it wasn't busy at all. We ordered the Pretty in Pink pizza which was phenomenal. They also have a nice specialty drink menu, too (I ordered something, but forgot what it was). They also have soft-serve ice cream which I didn't order, but is a nice little touch.  For the type of pizza they make, The StopAlong pizza is one of the best in Chicago.
It reminds me of NY pizza and dough. I would get fresh garlic on it too next time I come.

The stop along is a pretty decent joint for pizza and burgers, but I'd have a hard time giving it five stars for two reasons: it's kinda pricy for what you get (but I guess $12 to $15 burgers is becoming quite normal these days) and also, their burgers have a very distinct flavor you may or may not love.  They seem to season their patties with a ton of mustard. I personally hate mustard, so even a plain burger tasted pretty gross to me. I don't want a tangy hamburger.  I understand that's just my taste. If you're a mustard fan you might just like it. It just wasn't my thing and I don't think seasoning meat with that much of a condiment is a widely appealing choice. It might be your thing though. To each their own.
Fun little pizza parlor, good thin crust, good beer list. Video Games to boot.
Super great staff, and awesome food! Pizza and burgers are great

Love this place! Pizza is just the way we like it - thin and crispy (NYC style). The kid loves playing the $.25 video games in the back and loves the dairy free cheese on his pizza (dairy/peanut allergies). Stop in and check it out!

Overpriced chicken sandwich

Decided to try this place after review on Chicago's Best. Stopped in at 2:40pm on a weekday to dine in on my lunch. Only two other customers were there finishing up their meal. Before ordering I inquired the timeframe for a pizza and was told 10 minutes during the weekdays and 20 minutes in the evening, I was elated as I shared that I work in the area and was anxious for new spot. While waiting for my order I watched the employees chat and joke around and believed my order was in the oven. At this point I witnessed two people come in for a slice only to leave because the waitress informed them none were available as no pizza had been cooked. Finally I saw my pizza come out after 26 minutes and was told that was for a GrubHub order. I ended up leaving after I inquired where my order was the server checked with the Pizza maker and he had not even put in my order and the server disappeared. I guess this establishment values to go orders more than customers that choose to dine in. Wasted trip, wasted lunch. Try this place if time holds no value for you, it obviously is doesn't matter to the laid back staff.
Great chill spot..and food and drinks
Great drinks on the menu!
Great burger! Love the arcade games in the back
Food good service ok

Passed this place a couple of days ago. Was hankering for small cheval but the line was ridic. Came here and was pleasantly surprised.  Their burger was amazimg. It's like a mixture of small cheval and five guys in one.  The fries are soft and not too salty.  We also ordered a pizza. The pretty in pink (their pizza has pretty cool names that bring on the nostalgia) which had prosciutto, basil,  mushrooms, and vodka sauce. AMAZING. very close to one I had in N.Y.  The service was awesome, and I'd gladly come back.

Nice people here. They really tout their burger but I just don't think its near Small Chevals a block away. Every time I've tried it the bottom bun is just dripping with butter. Pizza has been consistently solid in-house.

The stop along burger is one of the best in the area. In the summer you can avoid the long lines at nearby burger places and come here instead. It's a classic double thin patty, mustard, cheese, and caramelized onions on a toasted bun with their special sauce. Get the special with a beer + shot and enjoy. If you have space for dessert, the vanilla soft serve with olive oil and sea salt is a good combo of flavors.
Had a burger and fries. Both were awesome plus they have great drink deals every day of the week, including weekends.

Let me first come clean, I'm from the Northeast and really don't dig Chicago style pizza, so I'm always looking for a good place to get a New York slice. This is definitely one of the best places I've found so far. We got the Major Payne and the Sho Nuff pizzas. Both were really good, but I'd give a slight nod to the Major Payne. It had pepperoni, jalepenos, garlic, and cilantro and had a nice kick to it. Their ranch dressing was really good too. It may have been house made and had a strong taste of dill to it, which I really liked. Then on to dessert. They have soft serve vanilla ice cream with olive oil and sea salt. I was taken by surprise for sire, but decided to give it a try and damn if it wasn't really good. The sea salt seemed to cut through the sweetness really nicely and was REALLY good. Our server, K.B., was really awesome too. I'll be back as often as possible.

I seen this place on Chicago’s Best tv show. Went to give it a try, I see why it was on the show, I ABSOLUTELY LOVED IT!!!! I had the Felicity pizza and it was soooo GOODDDD, even the desserts were good!!!  Good environment, good service, they very attentive. I will definitely go back! Best restaurant in that área. Trust me!

Great place!  The pizza is awesome, the appetizers are delicious, and the beer specials are cheap.  If you're in the area and want some good food, go here.

I got the veg burger. Pattie was good, but the entire burger was extremely underwhelming, with the pattie being the only source of flavor. A delectable sauce to accompany would have come a long way. But the biggest disappointment in this ensemble was the burnt fries. I'd recommend other spots for a burger fix.
Delicious burgers and pizza! Went back twice in the same week. Their specials are also really great - $15  for a burger, shot and a beer everyday you can't beat it.

Nice bar. Clean. Good selection of craft beers. Street parking. Clean bathrooms. Pizza by the slice is available. Stopped here after finishing a handyman job nearby. Interesting selection of  "digestife" type liquors. Menu also include salads and burgers.

They serve vary good food with a vary chill atmosphere... Had a pizza that was the best I've had in a long time , the waiter was real friendly, and the action figures on the wall along with the cool music made it a comfortable experience. I will definitely go back and recommend to all my friend's.
Great spot to eat in or order out. Awesome to have in the neighborhood!
Love the stop along! So great for groups and families!!
Solid burger. Awesome pizza and calzones. The bar now has scotch so 5 star. YUM!

I’ve only been here twice, but both times it was delicious and I plan to make this a regular spot. The first time I had the Stop Along burger, which was hands down one of the best that I have tried in the city. My friend ranks it above Small Cheval, but I don’t know if you can rank the two next to one another (very different flavors). Needless to say, it is definitely worth trying. Our second time around, I had their calzone. It was buttered up, seasoned with garlic, and smelled glorious. Personally, I think it could have used a a little more on the “inside”, but I am not complaining... I left there a happy camper! If you ever find yourself walking the 606 and catch a delicious whiff of pizza, you’ll know the Stop Along is close by. Give it a try if you’re in the area! Cool ambience, beer specials, and tasty food make it a must!
Cool spot off the 606!
Great spot for pizza and beer!

This place is great. Super yummy pizza, cool retro 80's decor, old arcade games in the back, and a full bar. But you must try the vanilla soft serve ice cream with sea salt and olive oil. It sounds weird, but it's smashing.

The most delicious pizza, we go here often!
Good pizza
Good spot- great drink specials even on the weekend, pizza was delicious. Thin with some tasty crust. Cool atmosphere, but a little small.
Great pizza and atmosphere!
love them!!

Ok.... this place was completely under my radar. My husband wanted to try this "burger stand" he had heard good things about. Ugh- great, good thing I was not hungry.... happy I am not hungry, notvtge most appealing thing to me. But yo my sheer delight, this was NOT a stand, but a small colorful restaurant, with a bar no less!  Upon viewing the menu, I see a slew of solid ingredients.... wait, this is borderline fancy pants. My husband ordered the burger, this is the best old fashioned burger I have had. It is perfect. My other favs in the city reside at The Bristol and The Dawson. I can not help but fall in love with the smells of NY pizza, the 80's iconic memorabilia, the arcade (small, but good). I order a glass of Pino (solid). I decide to order a pizza,  Space Balls. Whipped ricotta, basil, sausage.  I have not had pizza like this ever in Chicago. Every time I see NY pizza here, there is a sogginess no self respecting New Yorker would tolerate. This pizza is amazing, a crisp chewiness, that brings me back to great nights in NYC.  I seriously love this place. And the staff, completely out of this world.  If you are looking for a place with truly solid food, beautiful ingredients, a fantastic staff, real cocktails, cute wine selection, ahhhhhhmazing pizza, and gorgeous burgers.... but you don't feel like getting dolled up, go here for the best casual experience imaginable.  P.S. Prices are shockingly low. We ended up getting another 10 inch pie for the kids. 2 pies, 1 burger w/fries, 1 glass pino, good music, smiles and conversation.... only $51! I can not believe this hidden gem.
Everything was amazing !!! Great service great food just amazing
Been here 5 times in the last month. Very Friendly & they converted me into a Buffalo chicken pizza fan. Very Family friendly & phenomenal hambugers!

Watched the Cubs lose to the Dodgers on a very stormy night. The bar was quiet at the time, with a fairly steady stream of carry-out orders. The drinks were made with care, and the service was very friendly and attentive. We even were offered shots of Mallort with the rest of the staff! Really felt at home here. Now on to the food...the Pizza was one of the best I've ever had, and for the price, I could not be happier with this choice. 16" Major Payne pizza so delicious and just enough for my friend and me! I had some great beer and pizza with good company and did not break the bank. I could even take the 606 back home! SO GREAT!!!
Amazing pizza, atmosphere and interior design!
Decent thin crust pizza, yellow subway tile and 80s paraphernalia with a chill atmosphere
(Translated by Google) Great pizza, you should stop by. Great pizza!  (Original) Odlicna pizza, treba svratiti. Great pizza!
the pizza is great
Tasty pizza
Delicious 🍕🍺🍔!
This place is great!

Great pizza. Great burgers. Great music. Great, well... Everything.  This place is family friendly. This place is great to go on a date. Bring your SO, your grandparents, your parents, your kids, your friends, or go by yourself!

The place is super cute and the owner and staff are very nice. I enjoyed the pizza (though, when haven't I?) and tried a few of the regional beers on their menu, then hopped in the back with my boys to plug some quarters into their arcade machines. The Stop Along isn't an arcade or barcade in the full sense, as they only had about 4 games when I was there. But the vibe is great. Definitely worth checking out.
The food was tasty. It's close to the 606 park and the train station. They have nice 1980s mementos throughout the restaurant.

We watched the Cubs win the World Series here, which means I'll love this place forever. The pizza is delicious, their cocktails are inventive and strong, and it's probably the only place in the neighborhood that is fun for kids and for adults at the same time.

If you stroll the 606, this is the place to check out! The selection is great! The pizza is great and the staff is top notch. You will have to park on the street so be prepared. They just opened their outdoor dining which I have yet to experience. In the back of the restaurant are 80's and 90's video games sure to please. Around the restaurant is nostalgia as they have pictures of TMNT's and memorabilia from the 80's and 90's. The names of pizza are snippets from famous 80's and 90's TV shows like the Lambda Lambda Lambda. Enjoy!
Nice new place. Wish they had more.

Food was good. Kind of confused with what this place is supposed to be. Feels like a confusing mix between fast cheap food and slower more expensive items.  Owner was nice and talked to us directly about the neighborhood.
Fun atmosphere, excellent food! Great place!!! Try the calzones they are killer!!! Will be back

While I've had a pizza with fresher ricotta and prosciutto, the thoughtfulness behind each of the combinations ties these pizzas together better than the competition. The Pretty in Pink is the perfect blend of flavor and spice. Not one flavor overpowers the other, the dough and crust offer a little chew and alot of flavor. Next time will be getting a larger of that one and adding pepperoni. The burgers that people were ordering next to me looked pretty amazing as well. Definitely another time. If you have a sweet tooth the fresh baked dougnuts (yes you will wait, they are making them literally to order) with soft serve and honey is perfect. Do yourself a favor and add this place to your rotation, even if it is just for carryout. I know I have.

The food and atmosphere are fantastic. It's a fun spot to visit for a quick beer or a good meal. The Pizza is thin crust and terrific. It's chewy and crunchy and definitely great. The traditional Burger was a perfect example of a solid diner burger... Great place for sure...

The serve here was so nice and energetic she always came back and checked on our table she even started talking to us like a friend. The food is delicious but not a big menu, they have a small arcade room in the back.
Stop along for some classic thin crust style pizza and beer. Smoked mozz with pepperoni is amazing any time of day. At the time of review there were no reviews lower than 5 stars and I would concur.
Fun atmosphere and good food with decent beer selection. Kid friendly
Such an awesome vibe. The decor is fun. The food is delicious and this is a perfect spot to be next to a skateboard shop(Uprise)!!
Love this place. Great NY style pizza. 80s memoribila. Video games. What more can you ask for?

Awesome place. Service was spotty it was a busy Saturday night, but the food and ambiance was pretty cool. All 80's decor, games, posters, video arcade.  The burger was really, really good.  The pizza was great. Lone Star beer was a nice touch. Met the owner who was pretty sweet.
80s hardcore punk quietly playing, great arcade, great for adults & kids

Ordered delivery, can't think of any negatives to say. Went simple with the pizza (pepperoni), and a large order of garlic knots.  The pizza was fantastic, super chewy crust with quality toppings. The garlic knots, however, were the star show. They're on the small side, but good heavens, they were probably the best garlic knots/bread stick-type side I've ever tasted.  A wonderful addition to the Bucktown scene, can't wait to stop by.
The Shaka is awesome! Service is great as well!
Love the food and great service !!
Enjoyed the pizza and especially the salads. Will come again.
Loved the pizza, going to have to come back to try the burgers soon!
Amazing food and great drinks every time. I love this place.
Great pizza. Great burgers. Great drinks. Great soft serve. Great decor.

It was cold and dark, and I was in need of a burger. With a myriad of different options available, this place stood out as I walked down Milwaukee Avenue. Brightly lit with a smattering of 80s nostalgia, The Stop Along offers a solid burger at a fair price. As an added bonus, the staff is friendly and hilarious. I would definitely come back again!
Great food, great beer, cool spot! Small and intimate.
Damn--the pizza is legit. So good.
So many specialty pizzas (with delish veggie options). Loved the vibe and old school vid games in the back
Great new local place with a unique style and thin pizza!
Great pizza. Great beers. Great people. Go here!
Great gluten free pizza and cocktails!
Great burgers and NY-style pizza, accompanied by a well stocked bar.  Couldn't ask for more.
